            <h4>What is the current population of Ripley?</h4>
            <p>
                Based on the latest 2022 data from the US census, the
                current population of Ripley is 3,064.  Ripley, West Virginia is the 6,193rd largest city in the US.
            </p>

            

            

            <h4>What was the peak population of Ripley?</h4>
            <p>
                
                    The peak population of Ripley was in
                    1990, when its population was
                    3,339.
                    
                        In 1990, Ripley was the
                        5,189th largest city in the US; now
                        its fallen to the 6,193rd largest city in
                        the US.
                    
                    Ripley is currently
                        <span style="color: red;">
                            8.2%
                            smaller
                        </span>
                        than it was in 1990.
                    </p>
                
            </p>
            
                
                    <h4>How quickly is Ripley shrinking?</h4>
                
                <p>
                    
                        Ripley has shrunk
                        6.0% 
