                <h4>What is the voting age population of Ripley, West Virginia?</h4>
                <p>
                    The total voting age population of Ripley, West Virginia, meaning US citizens 18 or older, is 2,746.  The voting age population is 41.0% male and 59.0% female.
                </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Ripley, West Virginia residents are senior citizens?</h4>
                    <p>
                        According to the latest census statistics, 23.2% of
                        the residents of Ripley are 65 or older.
                    </p>
                

                
                    

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
