                    <h4>What are the racial demographics of Ripley, West Virginia?</h4>
                    <p>The racial demographics of Ripley are 99.5% White and 0.5% Asian. Additionally, 3.3% of the population identifies as Hispanic.</p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Ripley, West Virginia residents are below the poverty line?</h4>
                    <p>
                    In Ripley, 17.7% of
                    residents have an income below the poverty line, and the child poverty rate
                    is 0.0%.
                    On a per-household basis,
                    9.2% of families are below
                    the poverty line in Ripley.
                    </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Ripley, West Virginia residents are in the labor force?</h4>
                    <p>
                    Among those aged 16 and older, 51.3% of
                    Ripley residents are in the labor force.
                    </p>
                

                

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    

                
                
                <h4>What are the education levels among Ripley, West Virginia residents?</h4>
                <p>Among the adult population 25 years old and over,
                    92.3% of
                    Ripley residents have at least a high school degree or
                    equivalent, 21.5%
                    have a bachelor's degree and 8.1%
                    have a graduate or professional degree.
                

                
                
                <h4>What percentage of Ripley, West Virginia residents speak a non-English language at home?</h4>
                <p>
                Among Ripley residents aged 5 and older, 0.4% of them speak a non-English language at home.
                Broken down by language:
                0.0% of residents speak Spanish at home,
                0.4% speak an Indo-European language, and
                0.0% speak an Asian language.

                </p>
                

                
    


                
                
                    <h4>What is the unemployment rate in Ripley, West Virginia?</h4>
                    <p>
                        The unemployment rate in Ripley is 3.8%, which is calculated among residents aged 16 or older who are in the labor force.
                    </p>

                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Ripley, West Virginia residents work for the government?</h4>
